<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-600-686  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 600 686.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  August 15 1989 v3 n30 p18(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mitsubishi sharpens display in new 37-inch large screen. (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Battelle, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mitsubishi Electronics America Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Mitsubishi XZC-3715C (Video display module) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionDisplaysPresentationsMonitors.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By John BattelleandM;Torrance, Calif.andP;  -- Mitsubishi Electronic America Inc. this month introducedan improved version of an old standard in large-screen presentation display.andM;While the Mitsubishi XZC-3715C is based on the same 37-inch CRT as itspredecessor, the XC-3710, similarities end there, according to Craig Sloss,product sales specialist at Mitsubishi America.andM;According to the company, the new model offers improved focus over the entirescreen and more clarity compared with the previous model, as well as theability to automatically switch the video standard being used.andP;  The XZC-3715Csupports the Mac II, various IBM video standards, worldwide televisionstandards such as NTSC (National Television System Committee) and PAL, andVCR output.andM;The Mac II interface consists of a cable that captures the color video signalfrom Apple's eight-bit video board and converts it to an image on the 37-inchcolor screen.andP;  The system is used by vendors who wish to grab the attentionof passersby at trade shows, as well as by companies that need large-screendemonstration capabilities, Sloss said.andM;The XZC-3715C costs $7,599.andM;Mitsubishi Electronic America is located at 991 Knox St., Torrance, Calif.andO;90502; (213) 515-3993.andP;  n</TEXT></DOC>